This paper deals with Markov decision processes (MDPs) and their optimization under multiple long run average objectives. The paper discusses the use of randomized and memory-based strategies for achieving Pareto optimal values and epsilon-approximation. These topics are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
